column4: Hi again! I replaced my NETGEAR FA-310TX Ethernet device by a noname product with Realtek 8139 Chip, but it still doesnt work - dmesg says "pci dev 0000:00:08.0 (id 10ec:8139 rev 10) is not a 8139C+ compatible chip" - what do I have to do?
aris[doritos] : This is my second card which is not recognized, it really sucks :-(
are you sure it's not supported?
